=================================================
 
Documentary series following Britain's next generation of emergency service recruits as they embark on their new careers.
 
 

1/15 Amber's first shift starts with a bang - but her drugs raid doesn't go as planned.

2/15 Martin tracks down a man accused of assault, but will he make his first arrest?
 
3/15 Paramedic recruit Julie calls on all her training to save the life of a patient. 

4/15 Rookie paramedic Ben is faced with the kind of job even experienced colleagues dread.
 
5/15 Kelly's training is put to the test when she meets a child whose life is on the line.
 
6/15 Police special Sarah hunts for stolen property and makes an alarming discovery.
 
7/15 Rookie paramedic Ben races to treat a man seriously wounded by a chainsaw. 
 
8/15 New paramedic Mark treats a patient with multiple sclerosis whose life is on the line. 
 
9/15 When new fire recruit Brendan smells smoke, he smashes down his first front door.
 
10/15 When a house party becomes violent, Laurence has to restrain an aggressive suspect.

11/15 Fire recruit Brendan attends his first road traffic collision.
 
12/15 Fire service rookie Lianne responds to a reported blaze in a block of flats. 
  
13/15 Police special Amber sends in the dogs to help bust a suspected drug dealer.

14/15 Hairdresser-turned-firefighter Helen faces her first blaze - a whorehouse is on fire. 

15/15 A man flung into the air after being hit by a car relies on rookie paramedics Sam and Ben.
